First installer-created target smoke test, 2026-07-21

Artifact under test:
  successful installer workflow artifact
  source revision: 723e956

Scope:
  This artifact includes flatpak-selinux in its embedded offline repository.
  It predates the current working-tree installer-runtime Plymouth and GNOME
  background-default changes, so it cannot validate those visual fixes.

Observed standard-install path:
  - Anaconda partitioned the virtual disk and created the target filesystems.
  - The software phase reported "Downloading 1024 RPMs, 1.93 GiB".
  - The installer uses file:///opt/azl-offline-repo/; this is a local payload
    copy into DNF's transaction cache, not a network transfer.
  - Flatpak SELinux installation output was visible briefly, but no dependency
    failure or transaction abort followed.
  - Installation continued through bootloader, user, and initramfs setup.
  - The completed disk booted with no installer ISO attached.
  - First boot performed the expected SELinux relabel and reached GDM.

Interpretation:
  Read-only post-shutdown inspection verified flatpak-selinux-1.16.6-1.fc43
  and an active Flatpak SELinux module at priority 200. Its policy payload is
  module format 23, compatible with the target's Azure Linux policy tooling.

  The target has 1,025 RPMs versus 1,173 in the live qcow2. The difference is
  primarily expected live-media and installer tooling, rather than missing
  desktop packages. The target reached GDM with its intended persistent
  autologin account.

  Two target side-load defects were confirmed by the post-install log:
  - Copilot staged only an installer script, which tried and failed to fetch
    the actual archive during target configuration; its failure was ignored.
  - microsoft/edit was staged correctly, but the target omitted tar and the
    extraction failed; the profile still pointed EDITOR and VISUAL at it.

  The source now stages a checksum-verified Copilot archive, adds tar, and
  fails closed if either required executable cannot be installed.
